{"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/init()"]},{"title":"Instance Methods","anchor":"Instance-Methods","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/lock()","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/try()","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/unlock()","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/withLock(_:)"]},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/NSLocking-Implementations"],"title":"Default Implementations","anchor":"Default-Implementations"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnfairLock","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"UnfairLock is an appropriate lock for cases where simple and lightweight mutual exclusion is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"needed. It can be intrusively stored inline in a data structure without needing a separate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"allocation, reducing memory consumption and cost of indirection. For situations where something","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"more sophisticated like condition waits or FIFO ordering is needed, use appropriate higher level","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"APIs such as those from the pthread or dispatch subsystems.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The values stored in the lock should be considered opaque and implementation defined, they"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"contain thread ownership information that the system may use to attempt to resolve priority","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"inversions.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This lock must be unlocked from the same thread that locked it, attempts to unlock from a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"different thread will cause an assertion aborting the process."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This lock must not be accessed from multiple processes or threads via shared or multiply-mapped"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"memory, because the lock implementation relies on the address of the lock value and identity of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the owning process."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The name ‘unfair’ indicates that there is no attempt at enforcing acquisition fairness, e.g. an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"unlocker can potentially immediately reacquire the lock before a woken up waiter gets an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"opportunity to attempt to acquire the lock. This is often advantageous for performance reasons,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"but also makes starvation of waiters a possibility.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This lock is suitable as a drop-in replacement for the deprecated OSSpinLock, providing much","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"better behavior under contention.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Low-level lock that allows waiters to block efficiently on contention.","type":"text"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/objc(pl)NSLoc